            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "There was a lot of discussion about this last time , and I tend to think the arguments favour the conservative position. Particularly, the compatibility argument is very compelling. \r\n\r\nHowever, I would like to point out that one of my previous worries still stands: `<C-\\><C-n>` is an awful default in many keyboard layouts (Nowadays, I tend to use `<C-\\><C-n>` myself, although I preferred `<Esc><Esc>` before, but only because I switched from a Spanish keyboard to an English one). So, even if mapping to `<Esc>` or a variant of it is not a good idea, it might be good to consider some other mapping.",
