            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> `<C-\\><C-n>` is an awful default in many keyboard layouts\r\n\r\nI hear `<C-^>`, for buffer switching, is similarly problematic.  However, these are all just defaults.  Anyone is free to map a different key combo.\r\n\r\nThe benefits of `<C-\\><C-n>` are that it was the existing, standard way to get to Normal mode in Vim, regardless of which mode you're currently using and, less importantly, it's likely to be a key combo that won't typically need to be sent to applications running inside the terminal.",
