            "body": "@wsdjeg We know that, and also that if we implemented a setting like Vim it would provoke plugin authors to write incorrect `tnoremap`s before switching to either `<C-\\><C-n>` or `:execute` (latter is more convoluted to do properly) after bug reports from the users with non-standard setting. AFAIR initial issue did have `<C-w>` as a suggestion, but it was turned down during the discussion, only leaving `<C-\\><C-n>` for being universal and nothing else for `tnoremap` being planned from the very beginning and not added later (not sure whether planned or not, if there was any discussion I missed that). Adding an option was never a suggestion though.",
            "created_at": "2017-11-28T20:57:22Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/7648#issuecomment-347661076",
