        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> doing so will prevent one from using Esc with terminal for any other use. for example, if you are using FZF while remapping Esc in terminal, you won't be able to close the `:Files` window by Esc\r\n\r\nFor people who care about that, they can unmap this default. The point is that `:terminal` should be nice for the common case. Anyone who cares about ESC in fzf (which also supports `ctrl-g` and `ctrl-c`) is very particular, and \"trapping\" ESC for all the other times where you really want to go to normal-mode isn't a great tradeoff.\r\n\r\nWe could also ship a \"smart\" ESC like this: https://github.com/justinmk/config/blob/1811c74f9e18b47801d659b2078521a222de160f/.config/nvim/init.vim#L65\r\n\r\n    tnoremap <silent><expr> <esc> <SID>find_proc_in_tree(b:terminal_job_pid, ['nvim', 'fzf'], 0) ? '<esc>' : '<c-\\><c-n>'",
